last_episode_to_air.name: Legacy
last_episode_to_air.overview: With the end of the war near, Miep fights to keep Otto's business running in hopes the Franks will return home; after the Allies liberate Amsterdam, Miep and Jan dedicate themselves to finding the Franks and the other Jewish residents of The Annex.

name: A Small Light
overview: Twentysomething Miep Gies didn't hesitate when her boss Otto Frank came to her and asked her to hide his family from the Nazis during World War II. For the next two years, Miep, her husband Jan, and the other helpers watched over the eight souls in hiding in the Secret Annex. And it was Miep who found Anne’s Diary and kept it safe so Otto, the only one of the eight who survived, could later share it with the world as one of the most powerful accounts of the Holocaust.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Miep Gies, who believes she is just a secretary, is asked to hide the Franks from the Nazis.

episodes.name: Welcome to Switzerland
episodes.overview: Everything seems to be under control until Miep's dentist asks her if she knows a place to hide.

episodes.name: Motherland
episodes.overview: Laws against Jews are intensifying, landing two small children in Miep and Jan's care.

episodes.name: The Butterfly
episodes.overview: Miep tries to reconcile her old life with her new one but is forced to choose between the two.

episodes.name: Scheissfeld
episodes.overview: Miep and Jan’s marriage is tested when he ignores her plea to abandon a dangerous mission. After the Nazis suffer a huge blow at the hands of The Resistance, Jan must go into hiding while Miep fears for his life.

episodes.name: Boiling Point
episodes.overview: As Nazi crackdowns increase in Amsterdam, Miep must hide an innocent student from her new Nazi neighbor. When a desperate friend begs for help finding a way out of the city, Jan finds an unexpected ally and hatches a plan.

episodes.name: What Can Be Saved
episodes.overview: Miep's worst fear comes true when the Nazis raid the annex.

episodes.name: Legacy
episodes.overview: With the end of the war near, Miep fights to keep Otto's business running in hopes the Franks will return home; after the Allies liberate Amsterdam, Miep and Jan dedicate themselves to finding the Franks and the other Jewish residents of The Annex.
